Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm
wide chips (no need to peel).

Halve any thick @Tenderstem® Broccoli{150%grams} stems.

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, then season
with @salt{} and @pepper{} and sprinkle over the @Central American Style
Spice Mix{1%sachet}. Toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, pop the @British Honey Mustard Sausages{4} onto one side of an
oiled baking tray and bake on the middle shelf until golden brown and cooked
through, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw sausages.
> They're cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the sausages are halfway through cooking, place the broccoli onto the
other side of the #baking tray{}. Drizzle over some @oil{} and season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Turn the sausages and return to the oven for the remaining time.

When everything's finished cooking, remove both trays from the oven.

Drizzle the @BBQ Sauce{48%grams} over the sausages and turn to coat evenly
in the glaze.

Serve your BBQ glazed sausages between your plates with your broccoli and
spiced chips alongside.

Finish with a dollop of @mayonnaise{3%tbsp} alongside for dipping. Enjoy!